In modern React development, managing state efficiently with clarity and type safety is essential. One of the simplest yet powerful tools in our arsenal is the useState hook.
In this article, we’ll walk through a real-world React + TypeScript example using useState, explore how to handle TypeScript configurations, and use this to illustrate a mathematical concept—linear growth.
useState?


